# Dockge

Self-hosted **Docker Compose stack manager** (Vue 3 + Express/Socket.IO). Upstream: [louislam/dockge](https://github.com/louislam/dockge). This workspace is a **fork** at `origin` → `ssh://git@ssh.git.ivonic.ch:30143/stalder-n/dockge.git` (branch `master`). Version `1.5.0`.

Fork commits on top of upstream: npm audit/eslint fixes, v-html XSS hardening, Coder `.gitignore` for `.cursor/rules/coder_managed/`, multi-registry Docker login (Settings → Registry; `DOCKER_CONFIG` under data dir). Prefer recording further local divergence here when it lands.

## Architecture

- **Single Node process** (`backend/index.ts` → `DockgeServer`): Express serves SPA; **Socket.IO is the API** (almost no REST).
- **Stacks are files** under `DOCKGE_STACKS_DIR` (default `/opt/stacks`); SQLite in `data/dockge.db` holds users/settings/agents only.
- Docker work = spawn `docker compose` (not Dockerode). Interactive output via PTY (`backend/terminal.ts`).
- **Agents** = remote Dockge instances; UI targets host via `agent(endpoint, event, …)`. Empty endpoint = local. `ALL_ENDPOINTS` fans out.

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `backend/` | Server, Stack domain, socket handlers, DB |
| `frontend/` | Vue 3 SPA (Vite → `frontend-dist/`) |
| `common/` | Shared TS (status enums, AgentSocket, YAML helpers) |
| `docker/` | Image build |
| `extra/` | Ops scripts, healthcheck, templates |

## Dev / build

- Node `>= 22.14.0`. `npm run dev` → Vite `:5000` + backend `:5001`.
- Prod: `npm run build:frontend` then `npm start` / Docker `tsx ./backend/index.ts`.
- Quality: `npm run lint`, `check-ts`. No unit test suite; CI = lint + tsc + frontend build.
- BE deps in `dependencies`, FE in `devDependencies` (Docker `npm ci --omit=dev`).

## Conventions (from CONTRIBUTING)

- 4 spaces; ESLint; JSDoc on functions; camelCase TS / snake_case SQLite / kebab-case CSS.
- Prefer UI settings over env; env only for startup (`DOCKGE_PORT`, `DOCKGE_STACKS_DIR`, `DOCKGE_DATA_DIR`, SSL, `DOCKGE_ENABLE_CONSOLE`).
- When Dockerized, host and container stacks paths must match (e.g. `/opt/stacks:/opt/stacks`).
